title: Patient EXO1
extract_protocol_ch1: Collected peripheral blood was centrifuged at 2,000g for 30 minutes for plasma separation. Plasma was removed and diluted two times with saline. Diluted plasma was then centrifuged at 20,000g for 30 minutes to remove large EVs prior to ultracentrifugation. Ultracentrifugation (Beckman Coulter) was performed at 100,000g for 120 minutes using a Ti70 rotor to pellet the remaining EVs.
